# {{ project_name }} — Developer Onboarding

Welcome to **{{ project_name }}**! This notebook walks you through setting up and
running the project for the first time.

## Prerequisites

Verify all tools are installed:

```bash
git --version && python --version && bun --version && task --version && {{ container_runtime }} --version
```

## 1. Bootstrap the Project

Run the full bootstrap script to install dependencies and configure the environment:

```bash
zsh scripts/bootstrap.zsh
```

## 2. Start Development Servers

Start all services (backend + frontend + database + cache):

```bash
task dev
```

## 3. Verify Everything Works

Run the test suite to confirm setup:

```bash
task test
```

Check service health:

```bash
task health
```

## 4. Key Commands

| Command | Purpose |
|---------|---------|
| `task dev` | Start all development servers |
| `task test` | Run full test suite |
| `task lint` | Lint all code |
| `task format` | Auto-format all code |
| `task typecheck` | Type checking |
| `task docker:up` | Start containers |
| `task docker:down` | Stop containers |
| `task db:migrate` | Run database migrations |
| `task clean` | Remove build artifacts |

## 5. Project Structure

```text
backend/src/{{ project_slug }}/
  core/           # Domain entities, interfaces (no deps)
  application/    # Use cases, services, DTOs
  infrastructure/ # DB, cache, external services
  presentation/   # API routes, CLI

frontend/src/
  components/     # React components (shadcn/ui)
  pages/          # Route pages
  hooks/          # Custom hooks
  lib/            # Utilities
```

## 6. Making Your First Change

1. Create a feature branch: `git checkout -b feat/my-feature`
2. Make your changes
3. Run quality checks: `task lint && task typecheck && task test`
4. Commit with conventional message: `git commit -m "feat: add my feature"`
